Armstrong Bakam, Bauchi A lawmaker in the Bauchi State House of Assembly, Musa Baraza, is dead, The PUNCH has learnt. It was gathered that Baraza was killed by gunmen on Thursday night at his residence in the Dass Local Government Area. The lawmaker represented Dass Constituency in the House before his murder. The Bauchi State Police Command confirmed the incident on Friday morning. The state Police Public Relations Officer, Ahmed Wakili, said the assailants also kidnapped his two wives and one-year-old child. He gave the names of the two wives and child of the deceased who are still in the custody of their captors. Wakili gave their names as Rashida Musa Mante (40), Rahina Musa Mante (35) while the childâ€™s name is Fausar Musa Mante (1). He added that four empty shells of live ammunitions have been recovered from the scene of the murder. The PPRO, however, said a crack team of police personnel have been mobilised to the area to commence an immediate investigation to rescue the victims and nab the perpetrators.